{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e8bfe6fd-ce5c-4267-bc69-5ac37ac08455","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ba389b1e-2338-48c4-9507-622f59f78f98","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":300,"requestId":"0426:119996:17B70AC:1B0327C:69E81E65"},"id":"5364aee0-e4c8-4959-807c-1967aee2b93f","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:03:39.645Z","parentId":"eab06c40-6670-4afe-b9c5-9f00d64f9eba"}
